runs.comm: and he rips one straight through the batsman first ball, zipped through off a length and Tamin was cut in two as he tried to play to leg

slapped straight to cover and if this task was difficult for Bangladesh already, it's got even harder now. A back of a length ball outside off, Tamin didn't move his feet out to it, went to cut and got it off the toe straight to the fielder at shoulder height for an easy catch
back of a length outside off again and almost a second wicket, trying to cut again, it comes off a wild top edge that flies just over the outstretched right hand of slip and goes for four
fuller on leg stump, off the pad towards square leg
picked up off a length and smashed over midwicket, stand and deliver here, good timing, he was wacthing McCullum. Got this from outside off, one foot down the wicket and heaved into the on side
length just outside off, cut and gets a bottom edge that rebounds over the keeper for a single
full and was heading down the leg side, a swing doesn't connect properly and it squirts towards square leg
full, punched to mid off, looked good for none
comes down the pitch, banged in, and it's called wide, had to leap up to try and swat it away, missed
fuller around middle and off, turned to the 45 on the leg side
full, strikes the batsman in the crease, huge cry for lbw but he says sliding down, probably right too but the batsman beaten for pace there
off stump line, back of a length, chopped into the covers for one
slapped to mid on, didn't time it from a fullish ball around off stump
straighter, similar good length, worked wide of mid on this time
sliding across the left-hander, well timed back foot punch but a superb diving save at cover point by Williamson saves four
this time gets it through taking a step down the wicket and slapping a full ball on an off stump line past extra cover, excellent timing

tries to go off side again but chips it to cover point. Undone by a slower ball from around the wicket, he again gave himself some room outside off but was reaching for the ball angled in towards middle stump, was there too soon and it came off low on the bat and chipped to the fielder diving forward in the covers
fourth-stump line, left alone outside off
back of a length outside off, chopped down to third man
back of a length just outside off, goes to cut and gets it to point
huge swing outside off, a thick edge but spilled by the keeper that was bread and butter to any wicketkeeper, especially McCullum but it's burst straight through his hands
shorter and pulled for four wide of deep square leg, well controlled and just helped on its way
just outside off, fuller, dabbed towards point
low full toss and timed back past the bowler
off stump line, turned round to deep square
played in a similar way towards the same deep fielder
bit more width, pushed down to third man, wide enough of him to come back for two

big shot into the leg side but not enough on it and caught at deep midwicket by Kane Williamson running back, another smart catch from Williamson, had to judge that carefully, running back and around, held it well. Rahim tried to pick up a length ball from around off stump and didn't get hold of it properly
slower ball, back of a length around off stump, turned through square leg
back of a length outside off, cut at and missed
forward around off stump, pushed into the covers
full ball towards off stump, blocked forward into the covers
off stump again, flicked past mid on with reasonable timing
length ball around off stump, played off the inner half of the bat to the on side
similar line, knocked into midwicket again
played forward towards point
outside off and short, hooked at and missed
tried to turn a middle and off stump ball to leg, gets a bit of a leading edge into the off side, nearly chipped it back to the bowler, got square up
fuller outside off, a big swing and a miss

big swing across the line and given out lbw. Stood in the crease and tried to swing it to leg but missed completely and got hit in line, only doubt was height but Nigel Long though it wasn't high enough, probably gave it out for the shot, should have done anyway, it was appalling
outside off, another swing and a miss
just outside off, back of a length, pushed to point
turning away from outside off, pushed to short third man
played into a similar direction
fuller, blocked into the on side
a little more off-stump, pushed out through the covers
slapped across the line but it brings four past mid on, taken from outside off
long on now goes back so this flick towards him just brings a single
leg stump, turned to short long leg
off stump, played forward back up the wicket
shorter, pulled out to deep square leg
leg stumpish again, flicked to the 45, the charge through for a run
too leg stump now, in fact down leg for a wide
waited for and late cut to short third man
on the stumps now and dropped into midwicket
back of a length, skids on, played back to the bowler from off stump
outside off now and cut into the deep as the cover sweeper comes around
cut into a similar region, this time a slide is needed to save four, good work from Guptill at deep point
flicked out to deep square leg
skids on and nearly goes past the defences as it's late cut to short third man
straighter, off the pads into square leg
little short, pulled towards deep midwicket, lands a few yards short of the fielder
fuller and dropped into the covers
nicely bowled, squares the batsman up and comes off an outside edge past short third man, didn't know much about that though
off stump line, turned to midwicket
just outside off and full, played to cover
shorter and pulled out to deep midwicket again
just outside off, played towards point on the back foot
again hanging back and cutting square on the off side
pushed through a little quicker, comes off the pads to square leg
down the wicket and a lovely shot over the top all the way for the first six of the innings, fine strike this, sails over long on
dropped into midwicket but a scramble up from short long leg saves the second
hangs back and cuts to point
turned out through square leg
shorter and cut to deep point
step down the wicket, dropped in shorter and just defended back up the wicket
floated up on the leg stump, goes to sweep but misses
down the track, fired in full this time, dug out to long on
swung into the leg side, finds the gap between deep midwicket and long on but not enough power to get it to the rope
slower ball outside off, dropped through square leg
short just outside off, he got into a very awkward position but managed to adjust and hammer it over midwicket all the way for six! Super shot
just outside off, waited for and opened the face to third man, excellent stroke
straighter now and blocked back to the bowler
length ball, swivelled through the leg side
slower ball bumper, chipped into midwicket and it nearly carries to the fielder coming in
full and dug out towards deep midwicket
middle and leg line, slapped straight to long on. Not a bad strike but simply didn't get enough on it and it flies straight to the fielder who claimed it at shoulder height with two hands
length ball, played forward back up the wicket
leg stump, goes to sweep and misses, struck on the pad, going down
just outside off, flicked back towards the bowler
step down and a flat drive back to the bowler
waited for and cut to point
down the wicket, meets it on the full and gets it past extra cover for four, timed well that
back of a length, cut into the covers
step down and punches it on the full down to long on
tries to cut and misses from just outside off
slugged down the ground, and gets it wide of long on for a one bounce four, well struck and wide enough of the fielder
and there should have been a cheap wicket, slapped a long way up in the air, Vettori comes around from deep square leg and seemed to get there before letting the ball through his hands down low
swing and a miss to a back of a length ball
back of a length and heaved over deep midwicket, a big thump that, rocking back and giving it a right old thwack
much better, full just outside off, slapped only along the ground to long on
short again and a boundary again, taken from outside off and gets it wide of deep midwicket, poor bowling this
slower ball, full on the stumps, leaned out and driven to extra cover
just outside off, stays in the crease and chops it very fine to third man
fuller outside off and surprise, surprise, it's more successful, a swing and a miss

good strike down to long and a smart catch from Guptill that was travelling and could nearly have made him skip over the rope but it was very well held, powerfully struck but didn't get it wide of the fielder. Guptill leapt up and took it two handed above his head
full down leg side, anything on that it was four, but it misses everything
full on the stumps, backing away, angled down to third man
yorker-length outside off, misses attempting to drive
full again outside off, down the track and chopped out towards deep cover, wide of the fielder so two runs
full ball and chipped back over the bowler's head for four, lovely little strike that, picked up very well

stepped back and then forward and then chips a back of a length ball straight to short third man, didn't get anywhere near the required distance on that, simple catch for Franklin. Tried to ramp it over him but the contact was poor
around the wicket, a top-edged pull goes over the keeper for four
this is fuller on the stumps, blocked into the covers
full again and it beats everything through to the keeper as it was tried to be flicked over the on side
back of a length again, slower ball, left in the end and through to the keeper for a dot

length ball on off stump, chipped into the covers and extra cover takes it coming to his right, sliding and grabbing with two hands, easy chance well caught and a third wicket for Southee, Sunny trying to go over the off side and failing
backs away, bowls full and chopped into the covers, leaning out towards it
swinging away from the off stump, way too far in fact on a full length
very full, dug out down the ground for a single to long off
around the wicket, angled in, Razzak falls over as he gets hit on the thigh pad which runs down to long leg
full and swinging away, reached for and chopped out to deep cover
defended going back around middle and off
